                    "short_description":  "A historic coastal landmark of Alappuzha known for its long sandy shore, ancient sea bridge, and cultural festivals.",
                    "detailed":  "Alappuzha Beach is one of Kerala’s earliest developed beaches and a major tourist attraction in Alappuzha. The remains of the 150-year-old Alappuzha Sea Bridge (pier), once used for loading goods to ships, still stands as an iconic structure. Over decades, the beach has hosted major events such as the Alappuzha Beach Festival and Sand Art Festival. The beach’s scenic sunset views, clean sands, and proximity to the lighthouse make it a central hub for visitors exploring the coastal side of the district."
